div.h2: ISR Stack Frame: With and Without Error Code

g.text: RING-3 EXTENSION: Extra CPU Pushes When User-Mode Code Is Interrupted
IF=1 was enabled; iret restores IF atomically re-enabling IRQs
kernel code seg ring 0; iret checks CPL change via CS.DPL
fault: faulting instr addr; trap/IRQ: next instr addr
ISR_NOERR macro: push dword 0; normalises stack to match error-code path
push dword N; passed to exception_handler as frame->vector
ESP-32 -> EAX ECX EDX EBX ESP EBP ESI EDI [pusha]
8 x 4 = 32 bytes; popa on exit restores all 8 registers
ESP-48 -> GS FS ES DS (4 x 4 bytes) [software push]
pushed individually after pusha; kernel sets DS/ES/FS/GS = 0x10
ESP -> interrupt_frame_t* passed to C handler
ISR_ERR macro: push dword N ONLY NO dummy 0; error code already on stack
ESP-28 -> EAX ECX EDX EBX ESP EBP ESI EDI [pusha]
ESP-44 -> GS FS ES DS (4 x 4 bytes) [software push]
ESP -> interrupt_frame_t* passed to C handler
CPU switches to kernel stack via TSS.ESP0 THEN pushes two extra fields above EFLAGS
ESP+28 -> SS = 0x23 user-mode stack segment [CPU auto-push]
user data selector index=4 RPL=3; iret restores to reload user stack segment
ESP+24 -> ESP user-mode stack pointer [CPU auto-push]
user ESP at interrupt time; absent for ring-0 interrupts; iret pops to switch back to user stack
... then EFLAGS CS EIP (+ error code if applicable) as normal ...
iret detects ring change via CS.DPL > CPL; pops 5 fields instead of 3
2. Pop CS: checks DPL for ring change
3. Pop EFLAGS: atomically restores IF bit
IF restoration atomic with EIP/CS no IRQ window mid-iret
4. Pop ESP: restore user-mode stack pointer
5. Pop SS = 0x23: user stack segment; CPU now in ring 3
BROKEN: single stub, no dummy push for no-error-code exceptions
isr_bad: push dword 14 (vector only) / jmp common / common reads [esp+4] as error_code BUT that slot contains EIP / iret loads wrong address = TRIPLE FAULT, no message
CORRECT: ISR_NOERR macro normalises both paths
No-err path: cli; push dword 0; push dword N; jmp stub / Err path: cli; push dword N; jmp stub / Exit (same for both): popa; add esp,8 (pops BOTH vector AND error/dummy); iret
KEY INVARIANT: add esp,8 always pops 8 bytes (vector + error/dummy). Both paths leave identical layout for iret.
CR2 = faulting virtual address READ FIRST before any other operation
Bit 2 (U)=0: fault in SUPERVISOR mode ring 0
Bit 2 (U)=1: fault in USER mode ring 3 security check!

P=0,W=0,U=0: kernel read unmapped (null deref?) | P=0,W=1,U=0: kernel write unmapped | P=0,W=0,U=1: user segfault read | P=1,W=0,U=1: user read kernel page SECURITY | P=1,W=1,U=1: user write kernel page SECURITY | P=1,W=1,U=0: kernel write read-only (COW)
IRQ_STUB (vectors 32-47): NO error code; must send PIC EOI after handler; interrupt gate clears IF
Vector 0x80 (INT 0x80): NO error code; DPL=3 trap gate (user-callable); IF remains set during syscall
dummy push normalises: both paths identical above add esp,8
ring-3 interrupt: SS+ESP pushed above EFLAGS by CPU via TSS.ESP0
error-code exceptions also gain SS+ESP when fired from ring 3
vector 14: decode P/W/U bits + read CR2 immediately
iret pops CPU-pushed fields to resume
add esp,8 removes errcode+vector; then same iret sequence
